<CONTENT id="_800697_1"><TITLE value="Topic 1.4: The History of AI"/><TITLECOLOR value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;div data-layout-row="69ad57d9-8a0d-4358-b178-75d8b6a95770"&gt;&lt;div data-layout-column="476e72c8-9663-4e69-89e1-5f8394a4948f" data-layout-column-width="12"&gt;&lt;div data-bbid="bbml-editor-id_d52157c2-04a6-46c7-adb5-c8b57470c35c"&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Topic 1.4: The Foundations and&amp;nbsp;history of AI&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;h5&gt;Overview&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;As you go through this course and other courses in this stream, you will notice that many fields of other sciences are related to AI.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h6&gt;Watch this video, then go through the material:&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://mediasite.centennialcollege.ca/Mediasite/Play/e654ac96ea52472b980502045bec7c8f1d" data-bbtype="video" data-bbfile="{&amp;quot;src&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://mediasite.centennialcollege.ca/Mediasite/Play/e654ac96ea52472b980502045bec7c8f1d&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;alt&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://mediasite.centennialcollege.ca/Mediasite/Play/e654ac96ea52472b980502045bec7c8f1d&amp;quot;}"&gt;https://mediasite.centennialcollege.ca/Mediasite/Play/e654ac96ea52472b980502045bec7c8f1d&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span style="color: #1c8845"&gt;Disciplines that have contributed ideas, viewpoints and techniques&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Several disciplines have contributed over the years in the building of AI knowledge, the below figure illustrates the main areas:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-1692495_1" data-bbtype="attachment" data-bbfile="{&amp;quot;alternativeText&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;AI Foundations&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;linkName&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;M1_foundations.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;mimeType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;render&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;inline&amp;quot;}"&gt;M1_foundations.png&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Let's take a look at how these disciplines have contributed to the development of AI:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h6&gt;Neuroscience&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li style="font-size: 0.875rem;
          padding-left: 1.319rem;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 0.875rem;"&gt;How do brains process information? Localized areas of the brain responsible for specific cognitive functions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h6&gt;Computer engineering&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;How can we build an efficient computer? We need two things: &lt;strong&gt;intelligence&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;artifacts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h6&gt;Psychology&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;How do humans and animals think and act? “mental” terms such as beliefs and goals, arguing that they are just as scientific as, say, using pressure and temperature to talk about gases.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h6&gt;Control Theory&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Modern control theory, especially the branch known as stochastic optimal control, has as its goal the design of systems that maximize an objective function over time.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h6&gt;Economics&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;How should we make decisions so as to maximize payoff? How should we do this when others may not go along or the payoff is far in the future? Decision theory.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h6&gt;Mathematics&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;What are the formal rules to draw valid conclusions? What can be computed? How do we reason with uncertain information?&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h6&gt;Philosophy&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Can formal rules be used to draw valid conclusions? How does the mind arise from a physical brain? Where does knowledge come from? How does knowledge lead to action?&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h6&gt;Linguistics&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;How does language relate to thought?&amp;nbsp;Understanding language requires an understanding of the subject matter and context, not just an understanding of the structure of sentences.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;span style="color: #1c8845"&gt;When did it start?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Surprisingly, in 1950 there were great expectations and high enthusiasm. Let's take a look at&amp;nbsp;the various eras through which AI has passed so far:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://centennialcollege.h5p.com/content/1291106338081970598/embed" data-bbtype="video" data-bbfile="{&amp;quot;src&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://centennialcollege.h5p.com/content/1291106338081970598/embed&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;alt&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://centennialcollege.h5p.com/content/1291106338081970598/embed&amp;quot;}"&gt;https://centennialcollege.h5p.com/content/1291106338081970598/embed&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h5&gt;References&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Artificial intelligence a modern approach by Stuart J. Russell and Peter Norvig, Chapter 1&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</TEXT><TYPE
